DAMATURU – Damaturu Veterans Badminton Club (DVBC) have commended Yobe State Governor Mai Mala Buni for engaging youths in his administration through offer of appointments into various positions. Garba Aji Yabo, newly elected Chairman of the Damaturu Veterans Badminton Club revealed to Daily Independent shortly after his inauguration at the August 27 Stadium, Damaturu. According to him the Youths in the state have been carried along in governance “this is good for the future of the state as they are the leaders of tomorrow. This policy is really encouraging and has gingered the youth to further their education, we are indeed grateful and proud to be associated with his administration.” Says Ortom Had No Hand In Selection Of Ochi’Idoma -CPS 2023: APC Working On One Lie That Will Return PDP To Power… He used the forum to appreciate the outgoing Damaturu Veterans Badminton Club for sustaining sporting activities in the state. The Chairman assured to improve sporting activities for unity, body fitness and peaceful coexistence. ” We will continue to improve Badminton through improved partnership with Yobe State Government as symbol of the return of peace in the state.